{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Place butter, flour and icing sugar in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>.","Add 2 egg yolks and pulse <nobr>Turbo\/2 sec\/5 times<\/nobr>. Tip out and bring together into a flattened ball, then wrap in cling film and chill in fridge for 1 hour.","Roll out chilled pastry between two pieces of cling film, or on a lightly floured surface, and use to line a tart tin (Ø 22 cm). Prick base with a fork then set aside in fridge for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 190°C and clean mixing bowl.","Line rested pastry shell with baking paper and fill with baking beans then blind bake for 15-20 minutes (190°C) until golden. Remove baking beans and paper then bake for a further 5 minutes (190°C). Set aside on a wire rack and brush all over with remaining beaten egg yolk."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place lemon juice, sugar, butter and lemon zest in mixing bowl then heat <nobr>5 min\/50°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Without measuring cup, mix <nobr>2 min\/80°C\/speed 3<\/nobr> while adding eggs, followed by egg yolks, one at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid. Insert measuring cup then continue heating <nobr>4 min\/80°C\/speed 3<\/nobr> until mixture thickens like lemon curd. Pour into prepared pastry shell. Set aside in fridge to chill for at least 2 hours.","Remove from tin, then dust with icing sugar and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["120 g unsalted butter, cold, diced","175 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","50 g icing sugar, plus extra for sprinkling","3 egg yolks, from medium eggs, 1 beaten"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["130 g lemon juice","200 g caster sugar","200 g unsalted butter, diced","5 lemons, finely grated zest only","4 medium eggs","6 egg yolks, from medium eggs"]}],"id":"r137290","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-wLEs3XPZd00\/XZWfayVHQUI\/AAAAAAAAfEQ\/gN8NsRVPGIw93ySJVducy3am222bZe-MQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ukOA0OZ5xf9TXwia.png","title":"Lemon Tart","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.1 g","fat":"42.8 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"50.3 g","calories":"2608 kJ \/ 623 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, tart tin (Ø 22 cm), rolling pin, wire rack, pastry brush, baking beans, baking paper, serving plate, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["For a bruléed finish, before serving, place chilled tart dusted with icing sugar under a very hot grill for up to a minute until small brown spots appear on surface (do not let pastry burn). Chill before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","4h 30m","8 slices"]}